    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Step 2 — Gather Context",
      "description": "File reading instructions are vague and don't match Claude Code's actual capabilities. Says 'Check src/components/' and 'Read tailwind.config.*' without specifying how the agent should actually read files (no mention of read_file tool or glob patterns). This will cause the agent to hallucinate file contents.",
      "suggested_fix": "Replace with explicit Claude Code file operations: 'Use read_file to examine package.json, tailwind.config.js/ts, and glob src/components/**/*.{tsx,ts} to identify existing patterns. Handle missing files gracefully with fallback defaults.'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "high",
      "location": "Step 3 & Step 5 — MCP Tool Integration",
      "description": "MCP tool calls reference undefined tool signatures (mcp__ui-copilot__recommend_ui_sources, etc.). No error handling for tool failures, no schema validation for tool responses, and no fallback behavior if tools return malformed data. This will break silently.",
      "suggested_fix": "Add explicit tool schemas, wrap calls in try-catch equivalents, and define concrete fallback behavior: 'If tool returns error or empty response, proceed with built-in patterns and notify user that MCP enhancement was unavailable.'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Accessibility Baseline vs Code Examples",
      "description": "Contradiction between accessibility requirements and code examples. Baseline specifies 'focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-2' but Hero and Card examples use 'focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2'. This inconsistency will confuse developers about which pattern to follow.",
      "suggested_fix": "Standardize on one approach. Either update baseline to match the code examples (outline-based) or update all code examples to use ring-based focus indicators. Recommend ring-based for better visibility across backgrounds."
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Motion & Animation Table",
      "description": "CSS-only column lists 'animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-4' which are NOT standard Tailwind classes — these require the tailwindcss-animate plugin. This misleads developers into thinking these are available by default, causing broken builds.",
      "suggested_fix": "Either mark these as plugin-required ('tailwindcss-animate plugin required'), or replace with actual standard Tailwind utilities like 'animate-fade-in' with custom keyframes shown in config example."
    },
    {
      "severity": "medium",
      "location": "Step 7 — Code Patterns",
      "description": "Code examples use semantic color tokens (text-primary, bg-card, text-muted-foreground) that require tailwind.config customization, but no config snippet is provided. Developers copying this code will get 'class not found' errors if they haven't set up these tokens.",
      "suggested_fix": "Add a minimal tailwind.config.js snippet showing required color token definitions, or provide fallback examples using standard Tailwind colors (slate-900, slate-50, etc.) with a note to migrate to semantic tokens."
    },
    {
      "severity": "low",
      "location": "Z-Index Scale section",
      "description": "States 'Define these in Tailwind config as zIndex theme extension' but provides no actual config snippet. This is actionable advice without the implementation details needed to execute it.",
      "suggested_fix": "Add concrete tailwind.config.js example: 'theme: { extend: { zIndex: { sticky: 40, dropdown: 50, modal: 60, toast: 70, tooltip: 80 } } }'"
    },
    {
      "severity": "low",
      "location": "Design Pattern Sources table",
      "description": "References specific galleries (curated.design, landing.love, etc.) then immediately says 'Do not directly copy proprietary assets.' This creates legal ambiguity — are these galleries approved sources or just inspiration references?",
      "suggested_fix": "Clarify: 'These galleries are referenced for pattern categorization only. All recommendations synthesize common design principles, not specific implementations from these sources.'"
    }
  ],
  "suggestions": [
    {
      "type": "improvement",
      "location": "Step 1 — Understand the Task",
      "description": "Add explicit argument parsing for Claude Code's $ARGUMENTS format. Show how to handle multi-line input, file paths with spaces, and JSON-structured input if user provides it."
    },
    {
      "type": "improvement",
      "location": "Step 6 — Generate Agent Prompt",
      "description": "Define concrete complexity thresholds with measurable criteria: 'Invoke if: component count > 3, requires shared state, spans multiple routes, or needs auth integration.' Remove vague '>3 sections' language."
    },
    {
